1 processor shall hold in trust all payments received from the sale of milk for
2 the benefit of the milk producer from whom the milk was purchased until
3 the milk producer has received full payment of the purchase price for the
4 milk.
5 (2) For the purposes of this subsection, funds placed in escrow in
6 compliance with subsections (b) through (e) are held in trust.
7 (b) (1) (A) Except as provided by subsection (d), a milk producer
8 who sells milk to a milk processor may require the milk processor to
9 establish an escrow account for the benefit of the milk producer.
10 (B) If a milk producer requires a milk processor to establish an
11 escrow account under this subsection, the milk processor shall deposit all
12 payments received from the sale of any milk or dairy product into the
13 escrow account until the milk producer has received full payment of the
14 purchase price for the milk.
15 (2) (A) A milk processor required to establish an escrow account
16 under this section shall, on receipt of a payment from the sale of milk or
17 dairy products, deposit into the account a sum of money determined by
18 multiplying the total amount of all payments received by the milk
19 processor from the sale of milk or dairy products by the fraction
20 determined by dividing the total quantity of milk purchased by the milk
21 processor for sale as milk or dairy products into the quantity of milk sold
22 by the milk producer to the milk processor.
23 (B) The milk processor shall continue to make payments into the
24 escrow account until the milk producer has received full payment of the
25 purchase price for the milk.
26 (3) (A) An escrow account required under this section shall be
27 established for the benefit of the milk producer as a segregated, interest-
28 bearing account with a financial institution located in this state, the
29 deposits of which are insured by the federal deposit insurance corporation
30 or the federal savings and loan insurance corporation.
31 (B) If a milk processor is required to establish more than one escrow
32 account under this section, the milk processor may combine the accounts
33 into a single account.
34 (C) If the funds accumulated in a combined escrow account are
35 insufficient to pay all the milk producers who have not received full
36 payment and for whose benefit the account was established, the agent of
37 the institution with whom the escrow account is established shall distribute
38 the funds in proportion to the amount then due to each milk producer.
39 (4) On presentation of proof of identity satisfactory to an agent of the
40 institution with which the escrow account is established, the agent shall
41 promptly distribute any funds accumulated for the benefit of the milk
42 producer to the milk producer or, if required by an applicable federal milk
43 marketing order, to the federal milk administration.

