1 (5) This subsection shall not apply to a purchase of raw milk by a
2 milk processor until there has been a failure to make a timely payment to a
3 milk producer in accordance with section 3, and amendments thereto.
4 Once the entire amount due for the purchase is received by the milk
5 producer, the requirements of this subsection shall terminate in regard to
6 such purchase.
7 (c) Funds held in trust by a milk processor or in an escrow account
8 are the property of the milk producer.
9 (d) A milk processor is not required to establish an escrow account or
10 maintain payments in trust under subsection (a) or (b) for a payment if:
11 (1) Full payment of the purchase price is not received, and the milk
12 producer does not give written notice to the milk processor, by the end of
13 the 30th business day after the final date for payment of the purchase price
14 in accordance with section 3, and amendments thereto; or
15 (2) a payment instrument received by the milk producer is
16 dishonored, and the milk producer does not give written notice to the milk
17 processor, by the end of the 15th business day after the day that the notice
18 of dishonor was received.
19 Sec. 3. (a) A milk processor may not purchase raw milk from a milk
20 producer unless:
21 (1) Payment of the purchase price is made according to the provisions
22 prescribed by an applicable federal milk marketing order;
23 (2) any additional provisions are agreed on by both the milk producer
24 or such producer's agent and the milk processor; and
25 (3) the medium of exchange used is cash, a check for the full amount
26 of the purchase price or a wire transfer of money in the full amount.
27 (b) For purposes of this act, a payment delivered by a milk processor
28 to the applicable federal milk market administrator on behalf of a milk
29 producer in compliance with the terms of an applicable federal milk
30 marketing order is considered to be delivery of payment to the milk
31 producer.
32 Sec. 4. This act does not apply to transactions between a cooperative
33 association, while acting as a marketing agent, and its members.
34 Sec. 5. A milk processor who fails to pay for raw milk as provided by
35 this act is liable to the milk producer for:
36 (a) The purchase price of the raw milk;
37 (b) interest on the purchase price at the highest legal rate, from the
38 date that possession is transferred until the date that the payment is made
39 in accordance with this act; and
40 (c) a reasonable attorney fee for the collection of the payment.
41 Sec. 6. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
42 publication in the statute book.

